{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*User Story*

With the RTE Systems rotation including members across CA and DE beginning in Q4 2025, we need to remove the team from the [EXCLUDED_TERMS|https://github.com/hellofresh/opsgenie-automation/blob/master/plex/plex.py#L77] in OpsGenie so the DE-based members of the rotation got automatically compensated via Payroll.

This was fine previous to Q4 2025, as all members of the rotation were Canada-based, and they got compensated manually via a process followed by the North American payroll team. We now need this automation running to properly compensate the DE-based members of the rotation.

See members of rotation here: [https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1fdCqOKFMIJSQfXVfQmQaG1MiLU5BRDymsgmsNOlvKWc/edit?gid=1109514217#gid=1109514217|https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1fdCqOKFMIJSQfXVfQmQaG1MiLU5BRDymsgmsNOlvKWc/edit?gid=1109514217#gid=1109514217|smart-link] 
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*Acceptance Criteria*

* Update [https://github.com/hellofresh/opsgenie-automation/blob/master/plex/plex.py#L77|https://github.com/hellofresh/opsgenie-automation/blob/master/plex/plex.py#L77] to remove the {{"RTE Systems Squad"}} team
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*User Story*

As a HelloFresh or migrated Green Chef customer, I want to be able to switch between "Classic" and "Premium" plans within my account settings so that I can easily upgrade or downgrade my subscription tier.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria*

When the user:

* selects "Premium Plan" -> the user's subscription SKU is updated to the Premium Tier product family (e.g., {{NL-PB-2-2-0}}) via a {{PATCH}} request.
* selects "Classic Plan" -> the user is reverted to the standard product family (e.g., {{NL-CBT19-2-2-0}}).
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*Dev Notes:*

# *API Call:* Use {{PATCH /api/subscriptions/{id}}}. Payload example: {{{"subscription": {"product": {"sku": "NL-PB-2-2-0"}}}}}
# *Context:* This component is shared across Web and Native Apps (via Webview). Testing must include changing the browser user agent to iOS/Android to verify the view within the app container
*Reference:* See specific PR linked in PRD for similar logic: [https://github.com/hellofresh/web/pull/58257|https://github.com/hellofresh/web/pull/58257|smart-link]  
{panel}

